Java SE 12 & JDK 12
 

Uses of Package
java.security.interfaces

  • Packages that use java.security.interfaces 
    Package Description
    java.security.interfaces
    Provides interfaces for generating RSA (Rivest, Shamir and Adleman AsymmetricCipher algorithm) keys as defined in the RSA Laboratory Technical Note PKCS#1, and DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) keys as defined in NIST's FIPS-186.
    java.security.spec
    Provides classes and interfaces for key specifications and algorithm parameter specifications.
  • Classes in java.security.interfaces used by java.security.interfaces 
    Class Description
    DSAKey
    The interface to a DSA public or private key.
    DSAParams
    Interface to a DSA-specific set of key parameters, which defines a DSA key family.
    ECKey
    The interface to an elliptic curve (EC) key.
    RSAKey
    The interface to a public or private key in PKCS#1 v2.2 standard, such as those for RSA, or RSASSA-PSS algorithms.
    RSAPrivateKey
    The interface to an RSA private key.
    XECKey
    An interface for an elliptic curve public/private key as defined by RFC 7748.
  • Classes in java.security.interfaces used by java.security.spec 
    Class Description
    DSAParams
    Interface to a DSA-specific set of key parameters, which defines a DSA key family.
